      <PrimaryExemptPurposeTxt>THE CARBONDALE AGRICULTURAL HERITAGE FUND (CAHF) OPERATES TO PROMOTE THE COMMON GOOD AND GENERAL WELFARE OF THE CARBONDALE, COLORADO REGION BY SUPPORTING THE PRESERVATION OF AGRICULTURAL LANDS AND WORKING RANCHES THROUGH VOLUNTARY, INCENTIVE-BASED CONSERVATION TOOLS. CAHF'S ACTIVITIES FOCUS ON PROTECTING OPEN SPACE, AGRICULTURAL VIABILITY, AND RURAL HERITAGE WITHOUT REGULATORY MANDATES.</PrimaryExemptPurposeTxt>
      <ProgramSrvcAccomplishmentGrp>
        <DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>CAHF CONDUCTS ITS ACTIVITIES THROUGH A VOLUNTEER GOVERNING BOARD, IN COORDINATION WITH LANDOWNERS, CONSERVATION PARTNERS, AND LOCAL GOVERNMENTAL ENTITIES. ACTIVITIES ARE CONDUCTED PRIMARILY WITHIN A SEVEN-MILE RADIUS OF CARBONDALE, COLORADO.CAHF'S PRINCIPAL ACTIVITIES INCLUDE: (1) RECEIVING AND ADMINISTERING CONSERVATION FUNDS GENERATED THROUGH REAL ESTATE TRANSFER FEES WITHIN THE RIVER VALLEY RANCH COMMUNITY. (2) PROVIDING FINANCIAL SUPPORT, GRANTS, OR LOW-INTEREST LOANS FOR CONSERVATION PLANNING, AGRICULTURAL EASEMENTS, AND LAND-USE MEDIATION. (3) PARTNERING WITH LAND TRUSTS, COUNTIES, AND MUNICIPALITIES TO FACILITATE VOLUNTARY CONSERVATION OUTCOMES FOR AGRICULTURAL PROPERTIES.SUPPORTING PROFESSIONAL PLANNING, LEGAL, AND MEDIATION SERVICES THAT HELP LANDOWNERS RETAIN AGRICULTURAL USE WHILE ADDRESSING SUCCESSION ANDDEVELOPMENT PRESSURES.</DescriptionProgramSrvcAccomTxt>
